description: The TCA cycle mediates the catabolism of acetyl-CoA to yield two molecules of CO₂ and reducing equivalents in the form of NADH + H+ and FADH2. In plants, it is also an important source of carbon skeletons for biosynthetic reactions. Description from [Plant Reactome](http://plantreactome.gramene.org/).  Developed by Gramene.org.  Source: [Plant Reactome](http://plantreactome.gramene.org/).
title: TCA cycle (plant)
